<p><span style="font-size: 14px; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">We invite you to read Gartner’s <a href="https://content.pivotal.io/analyst-reports/hack-your-culture-to-drive-quality-and-devops-success?utm_source=pivotal-email&amp;utm_medium=email-link&amp;utm_campaign=gartner-hack-your-culture-q318" target="_blank" style="color: #00ae9e; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 400;">Hack Your Culture to Drive Quality and DevOps Success</a> report.</span></p> 
<div>
<span style="font-size: 14px; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Purchasing tools is not a substitute for adopting modern practices that lead to successful DevOps and transformation initiatives. Application leaders responsible for delivering digital business applications must reconsider their development culture. This Gartner report highlights practices that support successful DevOps initiatives, while addressing challenges that hinder it such as:</span>
</div> 
<div> 
<ul> 
<li><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">Lack of adoption due to deficiency funding for training and awareness campaigns.</span><br></li> 
<li><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">Lack of understanding between developers and business requirements.</span><br></li> 
<li><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">Lack of understanding of test-driven development and its value to developers.</span><br></li> 
</ul> 
</div> 
